subsection.p:
			Often, we write relation between components of \vec L and \vec \omega using a matrix multiplication notation.

				\begin{pmatrix}
  					L_x\\ 
  					L_y\\
  					L_z
				\end{pmatrix} = 
				\begin{pmatrix}
  					I_{xx} \amp I_{xy} \amp I_{xz}\\ 
  					I_{yx} \amp I_{yy} \amp I_{yz}\\
  					I_{zx} \amp I_{zy} \amp I_{zz}
				\end{pmatrix}
				\begin{pmatrix}
  					\omega_x\\ 
  					\omega_y\\
  					\omega_z
				\end{pmatrix}			

			While vectors \vec L and \omega are represented by column matrices, moment of inertia is represented by a 3\times 3 square  matrix. We say that moment of inertia is a tensor rather than scalar or vector. There are other tensor type properties in physics such as electic conductivity and refractive index tensors.
